    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Mmh, how is this problem unique to us?  If this is happening, then it happens to any python project that installs executable scripts.  Granted, many python projects are indeed just libraries with minimal to no user-facing executable code, but still: nose, cython are two that immediately come to mind with this same situation.\n\nHow does everyone else handle this problem?  I'm not claiming it's not an issue, just thinking that somebody out there must have figured this one out...\n"
